Miscellaneous Highlights: Delhi Traffic Police has issued an advisory for the commuters ahead of the Australia vs Netherlands ICC Cricket World Cup match scheduled to take place at Arun Jaitley Stadium on 25 October.
The match will start from 2 pm to 10:30 pm on Wednesday.
There will be a diversion of traffic for half an hour after the conclusion of the match.
Entries of all heavy vehicles, including buses, will be barred on specific routes near the stadium.
Limited parking space is available for labeled vehicles in the proximity to the stadium.
Spectators with unlabeled vehicles can park at designated parking areas such as Mata Sundari Parking, Shanti Van Parking, and under Velodrome Road.
Buses can start their services 2 hours before the match and will continue till one hour after the start of the match.
Spectators using app-based taxis and other taxis will have to use the service lane on Ring Road between IP flyover and Rajghat crossing for drop and pickup.
To reach Arun Jaitely Stadium, people can exit from Delhi Gate metro station (Gate 4 and 5) and ITO (Gate 3,4 and 5).
